name: DUO [User Marked Fraud]
description: This rule looks for when a user marks any push or call Duo Authentication notification as fraud.

name: DUO [Bypass Code Created]
description: When other two-factor authentication methods aren't an option, a bypass code can be manually created. A Bypass code is a feature that comes in handy when there is a need to provide temporary access for a contractor or vendor, or when an employee forgets their laptop or phone but still needs to access their applications. This rule alerts whenever a DUO Bypass code is created.

name: DUO [Admin Delete]
description: This rule looks for when a DUO admin user is deleted.

name: DUO [Admin Created]
description: This rule looks for when a DUO admin is created.

name: DUO [Admin Reset Password]
description: This rule looks for when a DUO admin user's password is reset.

name: DUO [Admin Disabled]
description: This rule looks for when a DUO admin is disabled.
query: class=duo_auth eventtype=administrator action=admin_update status=disabled NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
